5:
Boy, it sure is peaceful today. No
assignments have come in either...
7:
Must be because of all the hard
work we put in to fight off yokai
every day!
20:
I get the feeling Alk and Light are up
to something they don't want me to
know about. You have any idea
what that might be?
23:
I was told to keep it a secret, so I
can't say.
26:
I saw people in town that looked like
yokai. Were they also transformed
by the Lord of Shadow?
29:
If you're referring to the little foxes, I
believe they were always foxes.
33:
Hm, you guys are friends with yokai
then?
35:
We do have a few yokai among our
circle of friends.
41:
Does that mean... some yokai are
actually good?
45:
No, that couldn't possibly be true!
Father said yokai are bad news!
52:
You've improved yet again. I
suppose it's only a matter of time
before you surpass me.
54:
Listen well, Kuramaru. From the day
you become a full-fledged
swordsman, I'd like you to wield your
blade to protect the weak from
yokai.
58:
Yes, Father! I swear to keep
everyone safe!
65:
Father couldn't have been wrong...
But this feeling I'm getting...
70:
There they are sneaking around
again! Now they really have me
curious.
76:
I wasn't told to stop you from going
after them.
80: You good person. I thank you.
84:
Whoa! What's going on here?! What
are you doing with that yokai?!
88:
Look, Kuramaru. This yokai had a
good reason for trying to steal
foodstuffs.
93:
He found this boy lost in the forest
and kept him safe... The boy was
probably abandoned.
95:
Since he had no idea what humans
eat, he decided to steal rations from
the village.
99:
A yokai... taking care of a human
child?
102:
B-but stealing is wrong no matter
how you justify it! This is just bizarre!
107:
We provided the food this time and
made him promise not to steal
anymore.
109:
However this all started, some
changes are in order.
114:
Hate to interrupt, but something's
come up. Samurai on the prowl for
yokai are headed here from the
village.
118:
Chances are they're gonna do a full
sweep of the mountain. We'll have
to confront them.
123:
Doesn't that make this the perfect
opportunity?
125:
We can return the boy to the
humans.
131:
What are you doing, Alk? That thing
is
135:
Calm down, it's okay. Have some
faith in Light.
141:
You'll never have peace if you go on
like this!
144:
But there's hope yet. There are those
working hard to create a world
where humans and yokai can
coexist in peace.
146:
Until that becomes a reality, I ask
that you leave the child in our care.
152:
Light... I'm not too sure myself, but is
this really the right thing to do?
156: We've found you at last, yokai!
161:
COME AT ME WITH WHATEVER YOU'VE
GOT, HUMANS!
166:
We need to put on a good show to
buy him time. I'll be the yokai.
167: Still wanna take me on, swordsman?
179:
No point chasing them at this point!
The yokai won't be coming down
from the mountains anymore.
183:
More importantly, we should bring
the child to the village. He's been
through quite the ordeal.
186:
Ah... Very well! We shall take our
leave then!
195:
You make a pretty good actor...
Thanks for playing along, Kuramaru.
199:
To be honest, I'm still not sure about
all this...
202:
Give it some time. You'll come to see
that you did right.
205:
I'm just glad we got to protect that
yokai and kid, I guess...
